  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      After having shown that postconditioning allowed a significant 36% reduction of infarct size
      as assessed by blood levels of myocardial enzymes in acute myocardial patients, the
      investigators objective is to assess the effect of postconditioning in acute myocardial
      infarction (AMI) patients on microvascular obstruction lesions defined by cardiac MRI images.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
